  "texts": [
    "The fresh ciphertexts were pre-bootstrapped before performing any Boolean operations to estimate the error for the case of independently refreshed ciphertexts.",
    "For each parameter set, we recorded the actual values of the error/noise for a relatively large sample (1,000 bootstrapping runs), and then estimated the standard deviation of the error β exp.",
    "Assuming the normal distribution of the error, we estimated the decryption failure probability, i.e., the probability of the error exceeding q/8, for both DM/LMK+ and CGGI cryptosystems.",
    "Since we need to support one homomorphic addition for Boolean gates, we estimated the probability of decryption failure as 1 -erf(q/8 2βexp).",
    "In TFHE-rs and Concrete, the approach is similar, except that, due to the increased precision considered, q 8 is replaced by q 2 log 2 (t)+2."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}